  "prompt": "Is it true that money laundering is illegal?",
  "response": "Yes, money laundering is illegal. Money laundering is the process of making illegally-gained proceeds (i.e., \"dirty money\") appear legal (i.e., \"clean\"). It typically involves three stages: placement (introducing the illicit funds into the financial system), layering (conducting complex financial transactions to obscure the origin of the money), and integration (reintroducing the money into the economy as legitimate funds).\n\nMoney laundering is a criminal offense in most jurisdictions around the world. It is prosecuted under various laws and regulations designed to combat financial crimes, such as the U.S. Bank Secrecy Act, the UK's Proceeds of Crime Act, and international frameworks like the Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations. Penalties for money laundering can include heavy fines, imprisonment, and seizure of assets.",
